commit.message: License file was missing.

Updates autotools files

The autoconf/automake files were outdated. These couple of small
changes adapt them for newer versions of the autotools.

Updates list of MACs

+320 new MAC addresses have been added in this update.

Updates translation script

The format of the file with the MAC addresses that we fetch from the
IEEE changed. Thus, the conversion script needed to be worked out.

Updates random number devices list.

The list of random number devices has been updated. Now /dev/hwrng is
tried first (hardware based generators interface) followed by
/dev/random and /dev/urandom.

Merge pull request #2 from thoger/1.6.0-bugfix

1.6.0 bugfixes

Change default action to show

Previous default action was to increment MAC by one.  This default was not
documented and is "dangerous" (changes MAC, change is rather subtle and easy to
miss).

This changes the default action to --show, which has already been the default
in Debian packages for a while, see:

http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=621494

Upstream bug report:
https://github.com/alobbs/macchanger/issues/4

Only use BIA option when setting fully random MAC

macchanger 1.6.0 added -b / --bia option to control whether locally
administered bit should be set on the randomly generated MACs. If this option
is specified, locally administered bit is cleared, and it's set otherwise.

This option is considered when generating fully random MAC (-r / --random), but
also when setting random vendor MACs (-e / --endding, -a / --another, -A). As
locally administered bit is part of the first MAC octet, which is part of OUI,
clearing the bit (default behaviour when -b is not used) breaks all these
random vendor MAC modes, setting MACs that are not for any recognized vendor.

This fixes makes macchanger set or unset locally administered bit when
generating fully random MAC.  Use of --bia option in combination with other
option than --random generates warning.

Upstream bug report:
https://github.com/alobbs/macchanger/issues/1

Documentation clean up

Get man page, texi documentation and --help output in sync.

Fix spelling error: endding -> ending

Reported in:
http://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=621698

Original fix by:
David Paleino <dapal@debian.org>

This updated fix makes macchanger to accept both --ending and --endding
for backwards compatibility.  Only --ending is documented in help outage
and man page.

Fix computation of mac list lengths

LIST_LENGTH macro assumed it's used on static lists, but it was used on
dynamically allocated lists instead.  As a consequence, it always
returned -1.

Fix buffer overflow in mc_net_info_new

Long device name specified as a command line triggers buffer overflow.
Replace strcpy by strncpy to fix this issue.

Reproducer:
$ macchanger -s `perl -e 'print "A"x100'`

Reported in:
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=641704
Merge branch '1.6.0'
Disable .dvi rendering
Formatting fix

Implement -p/--permanent. It resets the MAC address to its original,
permanent hardware value. Patch by David Paleino <dapal@debian.org>.
--bia's -b parameter wasn't recognized

macchanger was exiting with an error-code 0 even if something went
wrong setting the MAC address. This patch fixes the problem. Based on
a patch submitted by David Paleino <dapal@debian.org>. Thanks!
Fixes the man page. Patch by David Paleino <dapal@debian.org>
Randomness seeding was kind of flaky. Fixes it up.
Unifies error messages format
Clean up: Removes unnecessary newlines

Introduces the --bias parameter to make sure MAC addresses are seen as
'burned-in-address' when they are actually 'locally-administered' ones.

Fixes how the "BIA (burned-in-address) / locally-administered" bit is
handled. Now, all the random MACs will appear to be BIA.

Thanks a million to Daniel M. Drucker for his feedback!!
